The paper deals with complexity measures of Boolean functions and decision tree complexity, which are central topics in computational complexity theory. The sensitivity conjecture is a longstanding open problem in this area, and the paper presents new upper bounds for various complexity measures in terms of sensitivity. This suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
